com.here.platform.location.integration.optimizedmap.roadattributes.javadsl

Interface SpecialTrafficAreaCategories


  • public interface SpecialTrafficAreaCategories
    Identifies specific road intersection types that a driver perceives as a single intersection. This attribute supports both map display and manoeuvre explication.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static SpecialTrafficAreaCategory ROUNDABOUT
      A circular junction where traffic moves in one direction.
      static SpecialTrafficAreaCategory SPECIAL_TRAFFIC_FIGURE
      A somewhat circular intersection that controls the traffic flow from incoming roads.
      static SpecialTrafficAreaCategory UNDEFINED_TRAFFIC_INTERNAL
      A paved area where a vehicle can travel, but there are no legally defined traffic paths.
